<div class="question-card"><div class="question-header"><span class="q-number">Q 2(3)</span></div><div class="question-body"><div class="question-text"><p>Let A = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}. Insert the appropriate symbol <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>∈</mo></math> or <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>∉</mo></math> in the blank space: 0. . .A</p></div></div><div class="answer-section"><div class="solution-block"><div class="label">Solution</div><div><p>A = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6}<br/> 0 is not an element of set A <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mo>∴</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>∉</mo><mi>A</mi></math></p></div></div></div><div class="question-actions"></div></div>
